<br>
Sure, AC will help you take less damage against melee hits, but what about non melee stuff?  Caster mobs don't give a rats arse what your AC is.  AE's don't care what your AC is.<br>
<br>
HP on the other hand will help you stand up to the mob you're tanking, by virtue of the hits taking less out of your pool, plus it also lets you absord more spell, DOT, and AE damage.<br>
<br>
HP is universally good.  AC is great...but it can't make the claims that HP can. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Marshall Haass Wolvesbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
